2.5. I asked how much longer the coffee to go would be after 20 minutes and they acted like I inconveniencing them.  Hate to give bad reviews nowadays but sometimes don’t really have a choice.

This place is so cute. I love their little latte art. The place itself is very nice. The artwork and tables are cool. We got three latte's. They were pretty standard. The foam art was beautiful. The setting was lovely. It was really just cute haha. The almond croissant was okay.

I arrive at this marvelous  place every couple of days because I like the special air that is characterizes this restaurant. The team is very helpful and professional. The service is very quick. Not to mention, the food you get is excellent. I have been there more than once and I was always happy. The price is honest. I highly suggest this restaurant to to everybody.

I celebrated my birthday today in this great place. Well we enjoyed a brilliant evening and the restaurant was absolutely the reason for that strong gathering. The crew  contributed in a very nice way, the cooking was great and my friends were extremely  thrilled. We shall absolutely come back again for more celebrations. thanks very much.

I live around the corner from Cafe Vienna and it is one of my favorite spots in LP! I regularly pop in for a pastry and am a big fan of their fresh OJ, waffles, and chicken noodle soup. Also, I wouldn't have survived this COVID pandemic without their coffee and pastries!  Thank you for being open and serving LP during this crazy time.
One of my favorite spots to grab some food. very good location, well organised, and good service. Highly recommended!
I tried this place before with a friend and I am hooked since then. I liked the fantastic character and delicious food and drinks. I recommend this place.
The best breakfast in Chicago. That's saying a lot.
Exceptional food, nice staff members, always excellent character. They charge affordable rates and the food quality is awesome. Great work.

Hidden gem. Always amazing quality. Super friendly staff.  Herb marinated chicken sandwich is the perfect sandwich and I enjoy regularly. The fries are also amazing... Trust me these fries are better than normal, and noteable.

Thought I was getting a croissant sandwich. What I really got was a giant omelette between two slices of croissant. Super good. Seasoned just right. The apricot crepes were fire and the coffee was really good too. I wish they would have checked on refills a bit more but the food deserves 5 stars. Will be back..

Love it 😍❤️ bread is fresh baked 👌 and amazing
This spot is worth giving a shot. They have large portions for affordable rates. Regularly well organized and with awesome character. Will come visit again.
The service is regularly prompt, fantastic vibes, welcoming employees. I will visit here again when I am nearby.

The Croissant Sandwich was really delicious and a huge portion - could probably be split into two servings. When ordering the sandwich and choosing your ingredients, make sure you list the most expensive ingredients first if you're ordering above the 4 it comes with because you'll be paying for anything after the first 4. I don't mind paying for extra toppings, but I just find it incredibly annoying that you could order the exact same sandwich with the same toppings, but end up paying different prices based on the order you list the toppings. You'd expect your waiter to do you a favor and punch in the most expensive toppings first to save you money or have the system automatically do it that way. I'm probably reading into the whole situation way too much but it really rubbed me the wrong way that this is how they treat one of their most popular menu items.

We arrived at this place for lunch. my friend recommended this spot.  Well, we were not disappointed. the staff were so friendly and we had a fantastic feeling. The meal was tasty. We loved this place very much and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Keep it up.

We enjoy to go out. Last night we came to this delicious place which friends told us about. We had a beautiful time there with superb cooking and an efficient crew and an impressive chief cook. We put this venue in our list  and we shall surely visit again very soon. We deeply recommend.

Chocolate croissants are stuffed with chocolate, whole pieces of sweets, coffee also very small. The atmosphere does not remind you of Germany or Austria. Bread selection heavily Americanized. Staff was very friendly, but this can also be due to the local tipping culture. Our search for good German cuisine continues  (Original) Als deutscher Expat vermisse ich natürlich deutsche Backwaren. (Translated by Google) As an Austrian three weeks on vacation in the US and in Chicago and then off to Café Vienna. I wanted to feel a bit of home and so I ate a Fritattensuppe, Viennese with fries and a Sacher cake. The soup was great. The rest not. The Wiener mit Pommes was far from what we know in AUT. Especially too much fat. The Sacher cake was a mix of Sacher and Schwarzwälderkirschtorte .. I do not know what, but it was not a pie that only gets about the Sacher. I was looking forward to the Austrian kitchen and was disappointed. The ambience was also far away from the Austrian culture. For me it was worth seeing, but Austria does not come over. Rather, a mix of Germany and Austria. Too bad, because we have such a good kitchen and culture ..  (Original) Als Österreicher drei Wochen auf Urlaub in den USA und in Chicago und dann ab ins Café Vienna. Ich wollte ein bisschen Heimat spüren und so hab ich eine Fritattensuppe, Wiener mit Pommes und eine Sacher Torte gegessen. Die Suppe war super. Der Rest nicht. Das Wiener mit Pommes war weit von dem entfernt, wie wir es in AUT kennen. Vor allem viel zu viel fett. Die Sacher Torte war ein Mix aus Sacher und Schwarzwälderkirschtorte.. ich weiß nicht was, aber es war keine Torte, die nur ungefähr an die Sacher rankommt. Ich hab mich auf die österreichische Küche gefreut und wurde enttäuscht. Auch das Ambiente war weit weg von der österreichischen Kultur. Für mich war es einmal sehenswert, doch Österreich kommt nicht rüber. Vielmehr ein Mix aus Deutschland und Österreich. Schade, denn dabei haben wir eine so gute Küche und Kultur..

Disappointing Experience -- Wouldn't recommend coming back!  1) New Ownership - Prior to moving out of the neighborhood, I was a regular at Cafe Vienna and loved coming for an affordable, delicious meal.  Apparently the original owners sold and there is a noticeable difference in the food and customer service (for the worst).  2) Food - The menu used to be hand-made Austrian food and has lost it's authentic touch.  Pastries are dried out (potentially store bought) and the food used to be fresh, but has now become fast produced like a greasy diner (with more expensive prices).  3) Gift Cards - For my birthday, my parents bought me a $50 gift card because they knew I loved Cafe Vienna.  They will no longer accept gift cards, saying the new ownership changed merchant services.  Feels unethical and a likely representation for how the restaurant is now operating.
Excellent authentic pastries and bakery, plus comprehensive sandwich and lunch fare. Just wish they stay open later for dinner...

My mom and I had the pleasure of eating here on our last trip to Chicago! The food was delicious. The owners were attentive and very personable. I even stuffed a loaf of the honey whole wheat bread in my luggage to take home. Their apple streudel was not too sweet, and the taste of the apples was tart and perfectly overwhelming. My mom enjoyed the cherry tart and I took some spaetzle back to the hotel for my last meal in Chicago. I would definitely return and I even recommend to anyone who lives in the area or visits this beautiful city.

Traditional Viennese/Austrian bakery, the Cafe Vienna offers breads, pastries and other confections. Plus it is a good place for breakfast, lunch, or dinner.  The breads stand out, and it is possible to sample then by requesting certain varieties with the luncheon sandwiches.  Those sandwiches are good values, too. Try the homemade soups, especially lentil soup. The Apfelstrudel is ad goid as you can get in Vienna. Likewise, the cakes are a taste of Austrian baking.

I came here for brunch, I do like the options they have available. I liked the coffee too, its Intelligentsia. We had the croissant sandwich and the chorizo scrambled eggs and decided to get the light and fluffy waffle at the end- the waffle was amazing. Very light and lots of berries. I wasnt the biggest fan of the chorizo but it would have been perfect for winter. They also have a really good sunflower seed bread- i might go back just for that.  the ambience is nice, very like a cafe with dark wood furniture. You can be sure to meet a more international crowd here, I heard a couple of new languages as I was waiting to be served. There was a lot of space available, they do have outside seating as well, so you wont be waiting in line. I might come back to try dessert. Once upon a time this was an ecellent Cafe with delicious pastry and good food both prepared in the European (German/Austrian) tradition. Alas, no more. The "fritatten" in the fritatten soup were as thick as my pinkie finger, and instead of being light they were more like lead. The "black forrest cake" deserved its name only because the dry cake was black and heavy, more like American devil's food in HoHos, and instead of a whipped cream filling the cream consisted of something again reminiscent of HoHos filling. Disgusting. In all honesty, I cannot recommend this place. The only reason it got 3 stars was because the staff is attentive and very polite.
Order crepe and after 20 mins, after that I saw their power went out. Came out from the cafe empty stomach. Power outage issue understandable but 20 mins to make a crepe ?

I've been here twice and I have mixed feeling about it. I've gotten cake both times and the first time was ok, wasn't the best cake I've ever had but wasn't the worst. I stopped in this afternoon and got two pieces of triple chocolate cake to go for a friend and myself. Let's just say if the cake taste like everything else that's shared a displace case with, it's not a good sign. Secondly if the frosting doesn't even taste like chocolate anymore it's way past it's prime. I have worked in several bakeries part time and know you generally try to sell the older things but there's also a date check to make sure if it's not selling before that throw out date, toss it. And unfortunately it did taste like cake that's been sitting in there since the beginning of the week. I think I will be sticking with  Vanille on Broadway and Melrose from now on.

The food is great, the price is reasonable, but I've had not one but two bad service experiences here. Just this morning I was in with my parents who were visiting and we had to have been the first customers in. It took forever for our meals to arrive and people who were arriving later than us were getting their meals.  The worst part is two of the customers that arrived after us at least 20 minutes or so ordered the exact same things we had. By the time my meal had arrived (The Construction) it was sans pancakes and I had to wait another 10 minutes + for them to arrive while the customer behind me got his order and pancakes. That was definitely the most upsetting part for me. I don't know what was going on but This was the second time and I felt like an a-hole waiting an hour for my food. I complained to the staff and the most we got was an offer for a free pasty and 10% off which was like 3 dollars.  It pains me to say this because I've never had bad experiences at night there, but I don't think I'll be back.

I've been to this place many times since I live close by. The food and service were okay when I first started going there, but they both declined significantly in the past year. If I eat in the cafe, the service is usually exceptionally slow. If I order takeout, half the time they would get my order wrong (using the wrong bread, missing sides.... you name it). When I called them to complain, they were unapologetic to say the least. My worst experience was last Saturday when I got a chicken noodle soup for takeout. The soup went bad already! I had to spit out when I ate and threw the whole thing away. It was disgusting. Of course they didn't even refund me for this. Well, never again. There are so many other good bakery/brunch places in this neighborhood. I will not spend any money at this place ever again.

Good food, a little pricey, the reuben is amazing

Possibly recently renamed to The Vienna.  Went here a Saturday morning. Ordered a banana, chocolate, and nougat crepe. I will be coming back here for many more mornings.  The service sat us immediately and kept our water and coffee completely full. Our cups were never empty. Food came out quickly and was very delicious and warm. The food is also very cheap! Service was incredible enough we wrote a message on the receipt and bumped up the tip. Loved this place. Really want to try the rest of the crepes and the rest of the entire menu!
